dude the trip was GREAT TIMES for sure! the food over there was pretty damn expensive!!! shiett son! we pretty much ate the whole time and every single bill was over $150.. well thats how they get tourists!!

well there was 7 of us total.. me, alyssa, chris, jill, justin, cesar and maria. we left oxnard around 5:30pm, and we didnt get there till like 11pm or something. we stayed at the Embassy Suite. one bedroom with 2 full beds, and a living room with a pull-out sofa bed. the hotel was dope!! we hit up the indoor swimming pool and the jacuzzi right away..

late nite munchies that ended us getting food at jack in the box..

continental breakfast at the hotel was fuckin great!! well it was free buffet shiet! i love bacon!

the aquarium was awesome too! A LOT of pix coming soon!! and VIdeOs too!!

we went on Highway 1 on the way home.. we pretty much lost 2 hours by driving there, but it was cool. had lunch at some cool ass restaurant right next to a creek in Big Sur. 

We saw a tow truck pulling out a car that went off the cliff !! Crazy shit yo! We had to pull over to watch it!! and the fuckin car was FUCKED UP! shieeet!

We had to go straight to Santa Monica cuz maria had an art show.. started at 6.. we got there after 8! hahaha. it was cool! ART KIDS are TIghT! and not those wannabe art kids either!

we had dinner at The Counter. it was pretty cool. we made our own burgers. mine was grilled chicken with bacon, lettuce, mayo, grilled pineapple in a wheat bun.. paid $9.50 for the damn thing, but it was worth it!

i pretty much got home at midnight! 

then i have work tomorrow at 11am at sony! i miss work! hahaha. i was off for 5 days! i need money!! plus i need to maintain my rank there! hhahaha. those fuckers cant beat me on warranty sales!! harharhar!!

all in all it was FUN!!! and we're already planning on going on our GRADUATION TRIP! it seems like everyone wants to go to BRAZIL!! we'll see.. its gonna be fun either way!!!!

im out bitches! later!

So i guess its time for an update.. i dont really go on this anymore.

- I got a job at Sony in the outlets! I've been there for only 3 weeks! I actually like it there! I work with Carrel and with Emery. Apparently he's the #1 warranty seller for 3 months straight! Shiieett son! I plan on beating him! We get commission on the warranties that we sell. Thats a pretty good motivation to do well at work. I think Carrel has over $150 on commission so far this month. I think I only have like $75 or something. It's really hard to get that number high since I think we only get like 6% or 10% commission on warranties. I'm trying my best. I'll try to catch up with him next month so it resets.

- hmmm what else? So yea I'm graduating this fall. Scary shit! I already applied at Harbor Freight as a Graphic Designer. I think they pay like $14 - $16 per hour. It just seems like the entry level position for Graphic Designers is around that area or $29,000 - $32,000. It looks a lot right now, but I know someday I cant live off of that. Web designers start at $45,000/yr. I'm actually going for that too! I'm really trying my best to be a jack of all trades. I also wanted to pursue Video editing and Film making, but I dont have time anymore. I just wanna graduate so I can work full time.

- In other news, my sister got the job as a manager at Target in Thousand Oaks. She's like the manager of the 4 floor managers in the store, and I believe there's 4 more managers above her. She's getting paid $52,000/yr now. Lucky biatch! haha. Thats pretty good considering she doesn't have retail experience at all. I guess that Masters in Business Administration paid off. That's a big jump from her $45k job at ITT Tech. Im happy for her. Hopefully she's gonna get a new car so she can give me her Celica!! harharhar!!

- In better news, Alyssa and I have reached our official ONE YeAR!! yayy!! And it's still going pretty strong too!!! Im happy! Happy as a duck! haha. We're planning on going on a bunch of trips this year. I think we're gonna go to a 2-day trip at Disneyland and California Adventures during spring break. Her friend might be getting in Hawaii this summer and we might go! That would be pretty cool (and expensive at the same time!) hahaha. 

- So all in all, life is fuckin awesome right now! I work almost 7 days a week, since I have 2 jobs (Sony and also at school). FUCK STATE PARKS! hahaha. I'M NOT GOING BACK! Shocking huh? I was there for 3 years!!  3 years too long!!!

LIFE IS GREAT. AWESOME GIRLFRIEND. AWESOME NEW JOB. 

-oh yea, I'm taking Life Drawing and we draw naked people in class. There's a guy who had 2 piercings on his nuts! He also has a MAn-gina! Disgusting shit!

Until next time.

i got a laptop! my first ever laptop! paid $1500 for this shit! here's the specs.. - dell inspiron E1705 - 17inch widescreen - intel core 2 duo (4MB/2.00GHz/667MHz) - 2 gig ram (533 MHz) - 256mb ATI Radeon (i should've gotten that geforce shit.. would've cost me like $200 more though) - 80gig 7200RPM hard drive (which is cool with me, since i have a 250gig external harddrive) - it'll also do an express upgrade to Windows Vista when it comes out in january!!! weeee!! no more Windows XP! - weighs 7.9 lbs its a pretty big investment on my part.. but it's worth it! i would've loved to own a 17-inch macbook pro, but with what i was looking for, it would've cost over $3000 of a mac to equal what i have with my dell. but someday though, that macbook pro shall be mine!!!!!!!
